<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-41-0705 </DOCNO><TEXT>The following are discussed: man's energy use and energy resources; fuelconsumption in ten world regions with respect to their populations; worldpopulation growth, projected to 2020; projected energy use in the developingcountries by 2020; world distribution of fossil fuel resources; and provenrecoverable reserves in terms of their annual consumption. Present productionand throughput of coal, oil, natural gas and uranium ores are described- capacity in all fuels is at a high level relative to demand. Commercialoperations involving these fuels can affect energy use over periods oftime, as has been illustrated by the oil industry in recent years. Thecomfortable supply situation relative to current energy use which pertainsat present must not be allowed to hinder development of new reservesand the building of new facilities. 5 figs., 2 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>